<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-03-29T06:44:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-03-29T06:44:00-05:00" n="628" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d628">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">882.20/436: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Liberia</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Walton</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Monrovia</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-03-29T11:00:00-00:44">March 29, 1939—11
                                        a.m.</date><lb/>[Received March 29—11 a.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>17. Referring to the Department’s telegram No. 8, March 25, 1 p.m., I
                                have corrected misapprehension the Liberian Government appeared to
                                have had.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Walton</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>